5000|$|Many have unusually low densities. The lowest one {{measured}} {{thus far}} is that of TrES-4 at 0.222 g/cm3. The large radii of hot Jupiters are not yet fully understood but {{it is thought that}} the expanded envelopes can be attributed to high stellar irradiation, high <b>atmospheric</b> <b>opacities,</b> possible internal energy sources, and orbits close enough to their stars for the outer layers of the planets to exceed their Roche limit and be pulled further outward.|$|R
